  "body": "## Issue\r\n\r\nMy use case is running `truffle test` with a fork of the main/rinkeby chain.\r\n\r\n## Steps to Reproduce\r\n\r\n[It seems like one can specify a network with a `fork` option](https://github.com/trufflesuite/truffle/issues/3257), so I tried this:\r\n\r\n```\r\nmodule.exports = {\r\n    networks: {\r\n        development: {\r\n            fork: \"https://eth-rinkeby.alchemyapi.io/v2/{myKey}\",\r\n            network_id: 4\r\n        },\r\n    }\r\n}\r\n```\r\n\r\nHowever, there seems to be something missing, since I get this error:\r\n\r\n```\r\n$ npx truffle test\r\n> Something went wrong while attempting to connect to the network. Check your network configuration.\r\n\r\nCould not connect to your Ethereum client.\r\nPlease check that your Ethereum client:\r\n    - is running\r\n    - is accepting RPC connections (i.e., \"--rpc\" option is used in geth)\r\n    - is accessible over the network\r\n    - is properly configured in your Truffle configuration file (truffle-config.js)\r\n\r\nTruffle v5.3.6 (core: 5.3.6)\r\nNode v14.16.0\r\n```\r\n\r\n## Expected Behavior\r\n\r\nUsing the config above, I would expect the tests to run on a fork of the alchemy rinkeby node I provided.\r\n\r\n## Environment\r\n\r\n* Operating System: macOS 10.15.7\r\n* Ethereum client: Using external node\r\n* Truffle version (`truffle version`): v5.3.6 \r\n* node version (`node --version`): v14.16.0\r\n* npm version (`npm --version`): v6.14.11\r\n",
